<html><head><meta name="color-scheme" content="light dark"><meta charset="utf-8"></head><body><pre>{"id":16,"date":"2023-07-16T06:29:03","date_gmt":"2023-07-16T06:29:03","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/melbacg.au\/?page_id=16"},"modified":"2026-02-17T11:06:18","modified_gmt":"2026-02-17T00:06:18","slug":"politicalschool","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/politicalschool\/","title":{"rendered":"Anarchist Political School"},"content":{"rendered":"\n&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Anarchist Political School&lt;\/strong&gt; is an introduction to the revolutionary ideas and strategies of anarchist communism. We meet fortnightly to learn about how capitalism and governments really work, how we can fight the ruling class, and why we need a revolution.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;All sessions consist of a reading, which we read and discuss together. There is no homework or prior preparation required. The Anarchist Political School is also completely free. All sessions are run in wheelchair accessible locations and nearby to public transport. Each discussion goes for 90 minutes.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;To participate and for more information,&lt;strong&gt; fill in the expression of interest form below&lt;\/strong&gt;, or send us an email at &lt;em&gt;melbourne@ancomfed.org&lt;\/em&gt;!&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;As of January 2026, we are currently running fortnightly sessions in Carlton and St Kilda. We no longer host the Anarchist Political School in Coburg or Ringwood due to capacity constraints.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-black-color\"&gt;Upcoming Sessions:&lt;\/mark&gt; &lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt;&lt;\/mark&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt;Carlton&lt;\/mark&gt;&lt;\/h2&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;ul class=